E.ON AG (EOAN) , Germanyâ€™s largest utility,
plans to invest 2.6 billion euros ($3.7 billion) in renewable
energy capacity through 2013.  The investment follows the more than 1 billion euros it
spent last year expanding its wind and solar capacity,
Dusseldorf-based E.ON said today in a  statement .  E.ON now has more than 3,600 megawatts of wind and solar
capacity. It plans to expand in Europe and North America.  The utility is building a 1,000-megawatt offshore wind farm
in the U.K. and is planning four offshore projects with total
capacity of 1,300 megawatts in Europe. It is building a 100-
megawatt solar thermal power plant in southern Spain with
